column2: Clear- lt. SE wind- no whitecaps
SUNNY- WIND OUT OF SE APPROX 5 MPH GUSTS OF 10 MPH
Clear- SW wind at 8 mph- medium algae
SECCHI DISK ON 7/18/91= 2.25FT.  SELF HELP VOLUNTEER.
Clearest I've seen this lake in 60 years. I'm excited.  Algae blooms- ice is off
LAKE MANAGEMENT PROGRAMS PURCHASE ORDER NRA 91826
Cloudy- clear water- little algae- milfoil starting- moss weed- swimmers itch
Sunny- blue sky- no clouds- algae bloom- lots of milfoil- swimmers itch better- less moss
Hot- sunny- no wind- no clouds- less milfoil- lake starting to bloom- swimmers itch.
Hot- sunny- no wind- no clouds- lake in full bloom- turned green overnight- less milfoil- lots of snails + bloodsuckers ...come see.
Air temp 80- sunny- moderate SW wind- lake pea green bloom- little plant life or milfoil- lots of snails and blood suckers
Overcast- moderate wind se- very little plant life- no milfoil visible- no dead fish.
Sunny- SW wind 5 mph- lake unusually green for early spring- no milfoil visible.
Found new deeper hole - 11 ft.  Was 9-10 ft. before.  Cloudy- calm- big clarity change since last test- no milfoil.
Depth 10.5 ft to bottom; no milfoil- light east wind- sunny
Lake level down 5" (170 last time) .  Sunny- light SW wind.  Clarity to bottom 10'.  Small amount milfoil N shore along Panyak park.
Overcast- no wind- Eurasian milfoil starting in other areas of lake rapidly.  Lots of algae.
Sunny- south wind- Eurasian milfoil spreading rapidly.  Large patch center of lake.  Lots of algae.  East shore pea green.
Overcast- west wind.  Lots of Eurasian milfoil on shore all over.  Seems to be dying off most areas of lake.  Lots of algae NE corner.
Lake level up from .70 last fall-8" up.  Ice off 3/16/95.  No surf weeds.  Lots of milfoil way up on shores-especially east shore.  Sunny blue skies.  Light east wind.
Cloudy- strong east wind- no milfoil on top yet.  Good musk grass bottom cover-small amongst algae.  Two white swans-lots of ducks.
Light east wind.  Milfoil + pond weed rapidly spreading over entire lake except north shore - looks bad.
Light E wind.  Milfoil and lily pond weed heavy on east side of lake.  Clarity up from 4' to 7' since 5/23.
No wind.  Milfoil + lily pond weed has spread to include middle of lake now.  Very little boating or swimming now.
Light east winds- clear sky- milfoil-pondweed cover 80% of the lake- harvesting started.
8 day harvesting contract 9500 channels harvested by my direction on board each day.  Algae bad.
Lake very clear.  Sunny- clear skies.  No algae.
Lake very clear. lilly pond with pad 2' from the surface in 1/4' water depth NE corner. new harvester to ( ) within 2 weeks.
Clear sunny skies- wind calm- some lily-pondweed starting to surface. number of sail boats on lake. good sign for minor weeds.
Warmer weather . pondweed thick southeast corner + entire east shore. our new inland harvester in service since June 4-holds 8-000 lb. per load x average 6 loads ada.-48- 000 weeds + water per day.
Cloudy-no wind. 80 % lake covered pond weed. red top milfoil coming three. harvesting 8 loads per day.
Sunny-windy southwest. minor algae appearing. fishing still excellent.
Sunny-wind calm-water in leaps-covered yellow/green. scum. harvesting rest of lake best as possible to keep up.
Sunny-southwest strong winds. lake in bloom. swimming in center of lake okay harvesting different type weed now-slimy green baby moss.

Sunny-windy southwest. clarity rapidly diminishing. shores (algae) look terrible. still harvesting under Department of Natural Resources supervision 24d was applied in front NE shoreline-approx. 100 ft.
Water down-clarity down-algae terrible on shore-green slimy.
Cloudy-light E wind-water level down-shores are terrible except by condos which were treated 24 d. killed 80% of weeds there-settled to bottom.

Sunny- water perception 3 because green water color Sunny- water perception 3 because green water color Sunny- water perception 3 because green water color  Sunny. Water was green and murky - perception 3  Sunny. Murky green water- perception 3
Mostly Sunny- low wind- no rain for 1 week
Sunny + calm- no rain for 7+ days
Sunny and moderate wind- last 2 weeks brought 4+" rain
